Cait's not here. I'm sad. I miss her. ! Here is your quote icon, my dear. I only forgot about it a little bit. Quick Question: Does anyone with a website want to affiliate it with Falling Night? I still haven't decided on the Semi-Friends Only thing yet.

New layout at my LJ and at Falling Night. They're both really really simple. I'm so tired of waking up in a place I hate. More on that later when I don't have readings to do. MRS. AMANDA URBAN-BANA!!! That's your belated birthday card, my darling! I'm giving you a printed out version tomorrow during Greek along with your gift, but the card looks much better in my opinion, on screen. Again my Photobucket bandwidth ran out. Stop hotlinking. That's all I'm going to say about that. I was thinking of making this journal semi-friends only. Basically keep the graphic posts open to the public, but the other more personal rants private and only viewable by friends. Any opinions?

Dearest LJ- Cait and I moved back into the land of bottled blondes and orange skin today only to find our mini fridge taken over by mold. I'm going to skip the part about how we scrubbed the hell out of fuzzy, smelly, green, yellow, and black mold with laundry detergent and how I ended up taking bits and pieces of the fridge into the shower to clean and rinse. Apartment searching sucks. And that's all I'm going to say about that. I have about 60 icons sitting on my computer right now for my Malfeas buddies, but since I'm a bit tired and don't have the energy to complete the set that is where they shall stay. I still have some to do a set for my ever so loverly Chip Sistah, Dena. I need to catch up on friends LJ entries and my comments lurking around here. :) But I've got to fix my classes first.

It's weird. I didn't realize how much I missed Priya until I saw her. You'd figure I would have already known. We talked all about school. Oh the good old times...Santa Claus and YTE. She laughed about the bottle blondes with orange skin. 

Visited school with Samma. Talked with Sacco, Chagnon, Murphy, McMaster, and Hedison. Good surreal times.

I'm off to look for mean Irish jokes. I'm part Irish.  Don't ask.

Wow. Could Photobucket be any more of an arse? No. I think not. For now the last few popular entries are linked to my server. If you want to see older icons...tough. And absolutely no hotlinking them. I'll hunt you down and tell my fat and lazy cat to attack you, but she won't because she's fat and lazy. Just no hotlinking. I started another set of icons since it's the only thing I can do lately with regards to art. But quickly abandoned them and threw them into the Recycle Bin once I saw the ruddy problem with Photobucket. I'm just too annoyed. Cait and Samma left a little bit ago after watching part of the 2nd season of Sex and the City. Cait and I are going to go see Birth tomorrow after she gets out of work. It's always an adventure with C-Lo--just don't hyperventilate, okay C-Lo? I should get a job this summer. Haha. Can you picture me with a job? Oh boy. I'll reply to all of the stray comments on various entries tomorrow. Promise. Luff Moi.

Cait, Samma, and I watched the first season of Sex and the City after dinner at the 9's. Cait over course gawked over moutain man and we all gave Yvonne some luff. Fun time was had by all and I even sang Phantom on the way home from dropping them off and hit EVERY red light. It's nearly 5:30am and I'm still up talking to Dena and Samma. Both of them are hilarious. Dena's planning a movie with the stoned and Americanized Trio. Tom is in there and he's in love with me, but you see I'm in love with Jude Law. He schemes with the stoned Trio to break us up and stop Jude and I from eloping in Vegas. So they race across the country with Tom desperately in love and the Trio desperately stoned. And the ending...you'll just have to wait till this masterpiece hits theatres. Dena would direct of course and get a bit of random screen time like Stan Lee. Ryan left because he wanted to sleep. He didn't get to hear this. Pfft. Sleep is for the weak. Ha. Ha. Give me 30 minutes and I'll be gone. And now Samma is showing me creepy ass pictures of ghosts. I'll kick your ass in Mortal Kombat for this. The icons were really popular. It's kind of weird. I spent alot of time replying to comments and questions on my LJ so I'll check friends LJs tomorrow, sorry my freaky darlings. This is what I do past 5am. Love me. E D I T: For people who have been asking me for the picture used in this icon- After searching through waaaaaay too much Mugglenet news I determined that it wasn't from Mugglenet although it was in my Mugglenet pictures folder. But finally I found the correct source. Here is where you can find the picture. I'm off to fix my credits.

Going to bed after 6am is never a good idea. I'm still wicked sick. I'm not going to make you sick with the sicky details. I got my Dad sick, too. I'm like a plague. 

I haven't been able to make any decent icons. I can't even spell my own name right. Gotta love the spell checker on LJ to catch all of my mistakes.

Thanks so much to <lj user="hakerrosenberg"> for my gmail account. She's such a sweetheart and she knows it. :) Now, my freaky darlings, go send me e-mails: sanapres@gmail.com

Vacation is lovely and I desperately don't want to go back. I still haven't decided whether to drop one of my classes and add Intro to Piano or whatever the hell its called.

Amanda-I miss you and we need to hang out and be geeky. Tell me when you're free and I'll tell you when I'm not sick. We can fix your LJ, too.

Mum's watching Troy. I may go join her or I may go RP. Decisions, decisions...

jafdj;*&#(*&$*(_)@#4KLJI

Mum bought me Phantom of the Opera tickets.

I think I'm making icons later on tonight because I have energy to burn. Getting up at 1 does that for you. Most of them will probably be of an older Draco for my GJ. Don't ask. I'm too odd for words. Bible, Lit, and Computer Science finals all went well. I think Bible may have gone the best...go figure. Programming...ugh. That was the hardest exam I have taken in my entire life even though we could use our books. I've never felt dumb with regards to school. That exam made me feel like I had learned nothing for a semester. Anyways. Cait, Samma, and I went out for dinner and then met up with Breanne. I got a bit of my shop on. I managed to squeeze into a size 7 in Hot Topic. I nearly died because of lack of oxygen. I could hear Cait outside the dressing room cursing me. I luff you and you need to buy the Cowbell t-shirt! I bought a Slytherin shirt (yes, we've established I'm a geek, thank you) and two pairs of pants. Now I'm home attempting to catch up on GJ and LJ. So if I didn't comment on your LJs I'm sorry. I swear I'm not such a bad non-commenting friend. I actually like commenting. Okay I'm going to stop rambling.

List of dumb things I've done in the past two days: 1. Didn't start studying for Klofft until...after midnight. BIIIIIIG mistake. 2. Missed EarthSea. 3. Ate nasty Charlie's food. & ate rice cakes & peanut butter. (Communion wafers with peanut butter, right Cait?) 4. Went back to biting my nails. 5. Didn't nap. 6. Rushed through my CSC final because I just don't care. 7. Lost my cladder ring. 8. Not yet seen Return of the King EE. Should have walked to buy it or called Amanda. 9. Watched Law & Order:SVU instead of studying. Episodes I've already seen numerous times, mind you. 10. Became extremely addicted to Roof Rats. 11. Spent 30 minutes turning my room upside down while looking for my keys. They were in the lock. The whole time. 12. Didn't study for my Programming C++ exam...but I'm not sure if this was dumb or not. We shall see, my freaky darlings. 13. & I finished studying at nearly 4.30am. I should've studied with Ryan. dumb. dumb. dumb. why am i so dumb? don't answer that. it's rhetorical. you know what i want for x-mas? a good dose of common sense. it's a miracle i can still style this late after attempting to memorize everything i can about the godman himself.

Who do I always steal my surveys from? Amanda! Dur. THREE NAMES YOU GO BY: 1. Jack 2. Malfoy 3. J-Dawg (Yes, I'm quite serious) THREE SCREEN NAMES YOU HAVE HAD: 1. crazzzy1691 2. jcpj911911 (My very first one!) 3. malfoi57 THREE THINGS YOU LIKE ABOUT YOURSELF: 1. My ability to be evil. 2. My writing abilities 3. My...er... THREE THINGS YOU DON'T LIKE ABOUT YOURSELF: 1. My forgetfulness 2. My procrastination 3. My lack of self confidence in my abilities THREE PARTS OF YOUR HERITAGE: 1. TV/Reading/Writing/Graphics--Some form of entertainment THREE THINGS YOU ARE WEARING RIGHT NOW: 1. Trans-Siberian Orchestra Tee 2. Jeans 3. My new slip on, black and white checkered vans! Explore artistically and writing-wise THREE THINGS YOU WANT IN A RELATIONSHIP (love is a given): 1. Attraction 2. Understanding 3. Hmm...Spontaniety TWO TRUTHS AND A LIE: 1. I will graduate college. 2. I never want to get married. 3. I hate driving. THREE PHYSICAL THINGS ABOUT THE OPPOSITE SEX (or same) THAT APPEAL TO YOU: 1. The eyes have it... 2. Smile 3. Working for some cooperation...this one is the most probable. THREE PLACES YOU WANT TO GO ON VACATION: 1. Greece 2. Ireland 3. England THREE KID'S NAMES: names that I would give my children??? 1. Draco! 2. Skye 3. Aden THREE THINGS YOU WANT TO DO BEFORE YOU DIE: 1. Travel the world 2. Finish a story 3. Sky dive Now three people I would love to do this... 1. Cait 2. Trist 3. Anyone of my newly added LJ friends
- - -
Cait is gone. ;( So sad. I talked to Amanda on the phone last night for a good two hours. I'm not a phone person that's a big step for me. Be proud. I am. She figured out that if we watch all 3 LotR EE then it will be 13.5 hours. I can't wait. I walk into Lit this morning...er...afternoon and see a nice lil present sitting on my desk. So, of course I'm grinning like a Chesire cat when I sit down next to Amanda (who gave me the prezzie). I open it up and I nearly burst! It was a Draco Malfoy shirt. *dies* I abosolutely positively love it. I think I'm going to wear it on Wednesday for my Bible and Programming exams. I need the most luck and encouragement I can get. Lit final was...blah. I spent two hours on the 10 literary terms. By the time I got to the essay my hand was in alot of pain. I did a half ass job on that essay. Meh. We shall see how well I do. I have a CSC final tomorrow. I don't plan on studying. That class is just too easy and boring for me. So since I'm not studying I get to watch EarthSea tonight. I bought the first book of the series and read up through the second chapter. Then I stopped because of finals. Damn pointless school testing me on things that I'm forced to cram into my brain the night before and will forget the following night. I'm off to finish my greasy and yucky Charlie's food while watching my Law & Order: SVU DVDs. I'll make a set of icons once finals are over--I'm thinking Thursday-ish me

I accidentally sneaked a peak at LotR EE caps...okay so it wasn't accidental. There is a lovely Legolas scene in there that I'm looking forward to see. :D! Dad went into surgery today and came out relatively quickly. Talked to him twice. He's doing perfect with the exception of a little post-op soreness. I would've felt better being there with him, but couldn't. But! No worries. He gets a month off to pester me and Trishy. In order for Cait and I study for Psych we had to walk all the way to Shannon's in the freezing rain. We had to hold onto each other because we were pretty close to falling on our asses with each step. Cait and I studied for Psych like banshees in record time. It was only 70 terms versus the usual 120. I got a Final Exam Gift Package from Mum and Dad and Trishy Poo Poo. Giant cookie toped with frosting that says: "Study Hard." I would take a picture, but it's mostly gone and my camera isn't here. In other news: Mooshie (our Beta Fish) is not well. He's losing colour. Doesn't look good for him. E D I T: Cait and I just danced to Little Mermaid's "Apart of Your World" in bed sheets. Green and Blue sheets. We pretended they were fins. :( No camera. Sorry. Next time. I promise

Where did this weekend go? Suddenly I woke up this morning to a buzzing alarm clock at 7am. I jumped off the top bunk and nearly killed myself just as I do every morning. Walked halfway over to my wardrobe and then back to bed. Reset my alarm. No Psych by choice. :D I hung out with Amanda on Friday. We had a bit of a geek fest planning a novel and talking about books and gorgeous celebrities and everything under the sun. Finally I have someone to talk books and writing with! :D We must do it again! And she may have talked me into trying a different style of writing that resembles to Mrs. Roquelaure. Cait and I played WAR! that night. Guess who won? Guess. Go on. Me. Oh yeah. That's how I roll. Take that lost game of rock, paper, scissors! On Saturday after an insane 9am episode, Cait and I went back home and after getting all purdy we went out to eat at Olive Garden and then down the road to shop. We got our shop on just let me tell you that. We blared Backstreet Boys and sang at the top of our lungs. Good times. Almost everyone is done for X-Mas presents. I still need to buy for my Mum, Dad, and Trishy. And maybe Priya. I don't know if we are exchanging gifts this year. I'll have to check on that. Remember how I said no more procrastinating? That's been true since that last entry until today, but I'm justified. This ruddy paper is so ridiculous. It's going to be three pages of bullshit. Here's how my schedule went: Paper 1...BIIIIIIIIIIIIIG GAP...Paper 2...Paper 3 assigned the day Paper 2 was due...Paper 4 assigned even before we handed in Paper 3. This guy seriously needs to learn how to space out his paper and make the papers on things that we have covered. Finals are coming up. I'm dreading the Bible one. Now I really wish I did have some religious instruction instead of jumping into it as blind as I am. The rest should be fine, but Programming could end up being a bit more difficult then I imagine. He's tricky like that. Off to write my Bible paper about Paul's teachings about feet and eyes and gifts and speaking in tongues. I've seriously neglected the Nano novel. I feel guilty. Enough of that. I joined a bunch of icontest communities and entered all of the current challeges that were up. I'm proud. Why you ask? Frankly because I always miss entering them. I'm not good with this whole date/time thing. Ask Cait. And Samma. Cait tried in vain to teach me the proper way to tell time in Friendlys. That didn't go over too well. I'm going to tell you an amusing story. And I promise that in some way you will find it amusing. If not...then you suck. Let the story begin. I went to see Ramsey aka Point Shoes in her office about the Life of Pi paper. We worked through all of my problems with the most difficult choice of paper topics ever. Note to self: Pick an easier paper topic, ass. Anyways...I decoded her handwriting and tried in vain to attempt the essay that was worth 25% of my grade. This is where it gets funny. I procrastinated. Severely. I did everything else that I could think of to do besides that stupid paper. Sunday night rolls around and dumbass here finally decides to start the paper. There were definitely little breaks in between where I started procrastinating by going on LJ or any other stupid place I could think of. Now here's the kicker...at a little past 4 am I finished off the paper. Millions of hours of procrastination + 4-ish hours on the paper=5 pages that doesn't particularly prove my thesis. Pointy shoes is going to eat that paper alive. Utterly disgusted, I printed off the paper and crawled into bed. Guilty conscience attacks. I couldn't fall asleep until a little before 6am. Mind you classes start at 8.30 and I go until 2.30. I decided that while lying in bed, praying for sleep to come that I will no longer procrastinate. I've been in a funky mood for a bit and the SEVERE procrastination has just been contributing to it. Jaclyn's Procrastination...you're fired.

dear lj- i spent the afternoon pushing ms. caitlin around the campus in a wheelchair. she kept telling me to 'mush' while doing airplane hands. occassionally she felt compelled to slip into 'retard mode.' of course, yours truly couldn't remain serious long enough. hold please. she lost her eyebrow ring i kept laughing as we passed people. i blew our cover and then cait would laugh. sad truth--more people talked to us with cait in a wheelchair then on any day combined. i was out of breath after pushing the temporarily wheelchair bound cait and decided to let her roll down a hill. some old people passing us got mad at me and kept calling things out. cait kept yelling: 'i'm not sonny bono! i don't hit trees!' here's a little tip for everyone: if you hit a big bump in the wheelchair you go flying forwards. remember that. it's an important fact of life. we felt the dire need to take pictures. oh yes. there are picture to go along with this tale. we went into the IT center and took pictures in the girls bathroom, sorry, women's bathroom. finally we carried the wheelchair up 5 flights of stairs. flub dubbed around and then it was time to bring the chair back. i rolled down the hallway all on my own, unassisted, might i add, and only managed to crash into the wall twice. it was cait's turn to push me to the library and we had a good old time. though several times during the high speed pushing i thought i was going to die. remember that little fact of life? well i thought i was going to break my beautiful face. where would the world be without me beauty? no where. that's right. on the way back from the el library-o we sang eminem. mostly consisting of the lines about sonny bono. i don't know why she was so suprised to hear me sing eminem. she pushed me into a tree and proclaimed that i was sonny bono. he's our new hero. and trees. trees are our hero too. i have no more funnies to tell you. er is on. fin. me
